{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 220°C.","Place butter and chocolate into mixing bowl and melt <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile, grease 8 silicone dariole moulds (see Tips) well with butter and place onto a baking tray. Set aside.","Add sugar, eggs, egg yolks, vanilla, lemon zest and juice to mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add flour and salt and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b> or until just combined. Divide batter between prepared dariole moulds (they should be almost full) and bake for 12 minutes (220°C). Cool in moulds for a maximum of 2 minutes. Carefully unmould cakes onto serving plates and serve immediately with blueberries and créme fraîche (optional)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g unsalted butter, softened and cut into pieces, plus extra for greasing","230 g white chocolate, broken into small pieces (see Tips)","130 g icing sugar","3 eggs","3 egg yolks","1 tsp vanilla bean paste","1 lemon, zested (no white pith) and juiced","80 g plain flour","1 pinch salt","fresh blueberries, to serve","crème fraîche, to serve (optional - see Tips)"]}],"id":"r250030","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-4tIRkSJBq40\/XZWqijK8I4I\/AAAAAAAAfZc\/vu3wSOo2wFQNFWZG9-XAmLD9F0cdjg5KwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_O91JVVXd5ayBioUz.png","title":"Lemon and white chocolate lava cakes","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.8 g","fat":"38.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"38.6 g","calories":"2182.1 kJ \/ 519.6 kcal"},"usefulItems":"dariole moulds, baking tray, serving plates, oven","hintsAndTricks":["We recommend using good-quality chocolate for the best results in this recipe.","We used the Thermomix silicone dariole moulds (available in The Mix Shop™) for our lava cakes. Cooking times will vary if using metal or ceramic moulds.","You can serve this dish with thickened cream, if desired."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","30m","8 portions"]}